<emphasis box="[1363,1436,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">truncô</emphasis>
(“maim, reduce to a trunk”), meaning that a structure is ending abruptly as if cut across at the base or tip. This term is referring to the clypeus truncate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cherman" authorityYear="2021" box="[570,773,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Liogenys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis box="[570,773,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Liogenys truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
